1.System Design & Architecture
The Hospital Patient Management System follows a procedural programming paradigm in C++.
The program is organized into a main() function that drives a do-while loop, and four dedicated functions for each core operation.
This modular design separates concerns and makes the code maintainable and extensible.

2. Data Structure Design
The Patient structure holds three fields: id (integer), name (string), and age (integer). 
A global array patients[100] stores up to 100 patient records. 
A global counter variable (count) tracks the number of currently registered patients.
A C++ STL queue<int> (waitingQueue) stores patient IDs in FIFO order.

